## Test: throws auto-propagation
##
## When a `throws` method calls another `throws` method without an explicit `?`
## suffix, the compiler must emit `try` automatically in the generated Zig.
## Without this, Zig rejects the call because the error union return value is ignored.

class ErrorPropTest
    def inner() throws
        raise "from inner"

    ## Calls inner() with no `?` — compiler must auto-emit `try self.inner()`
    def outer() throws
        .inner()

    ## Verify cross-method propagation works end-to-end via try/catch
    def run()
        .outer()
    catch |_e|
        print "caught: OK"

def main()
    var t = ErrorPropTest()
    t.run()
    print "throws_autoprop_test: passed"
